  abstract = {This article delivers the dynamical cosmography of the Local Universe within z=0.1 (1 giga light-years). We exploit the gravitational velocity field computed using the CosmicFlows-4 catalog of galaxy distances to delineate superclusters as watersheds, publishing for the first time their size, shape, main streams of matter and the location of their central attractor. Laniakea, our home supercluster's size is confirmed to be 2 \$\textbackslash times 10\textasciicircum 6\$ (Mpc \$h\textasciicircum\textbraceleft -1\textbraceright\$)\$\textasciicircum 3\$. Five more known superclusters are now dynamically defined in the same way: Apus, Hercules, Lepus, Perseus-Pisces and Shapley. Also, the central repellers of the Bootes and Sculptor voids are found and the Dipole and Cold Spot repellers now appear as a single gigantic entity. Interestingly the observed superclusters are an order of magnitude larger than the theoretical ones predicted by cosmological \$\textbackslash Lambda\$CDM simulations.},
