  urldate = {2024-12-24},
  abstract = {We combine the Ly-alpha forest power spectrum (LYA) from the Sloan Digital Sky Survey (SDSS) and high resolution spectra with cosmic microwave background (CMB) including 3-year WMAP, and supernovae (SN) and galaxy clustering constraints to derive new constraints on cosmological parameters. The existing LYA power spectrum analysis is supplemented by constraints on the mean flux decrement derived using a principle component analysis for quasar continua, which improves the LYA constraints on the linear power. We find some tension between the WMAP3 and LYA power spectrum amplitudes, at the \textasciitilde 2 sigma level, which is partially alleviated by the inclusion of other observations: we find \textbackslash sigma\_8=0.85\textbackslash pm 0.02 compared to sigma\_8=0.80 \textbackslash pm 0.03 without LYA. For the slope we find ns=0.965\textbackslash pm0.012. We find no evidence for the running of the spectral index in the combined analysis, dn/dln k=-(1.5\textbackslash pm 1.2) x 10\textasciicircum\textbraceleft -2\textbraceright, in agreement with inflation. The limits on the sum of neutrino masses are significantly improved: \$\textbackslash sum m\_\textbraceleft\textbackslash nu\textbraceright{$<$}0.17\textbackslash eV\$ at 95\% ({$<$}0.32eV at 99.9\%). This result, when combined with atmospheric and solar neutrino mixing constraints, requires that the neutrino masses cannot be degenerate, m\_3/m\_1{$>$}1.3 (95\% c.l.). Assuming a thermalized fourth neutrino we find m\_s{$<$}0.26\textbackslash eV at 95\% c.l. and such neutrino cannot be an explanation for the LSND results. In the limits of massless neutrinos we obtain the effective number of neutrinos N\_\textbackslash nu\textasciicircum\textbraceleft\textbackslash rm eff\textbraceright =5.3\textasciicircum\textbraceleft +0.4\textbraceright\_\textbraceleft -0.6\textbraceright\textbraceleft\textbraceright\textasciicircum\textbraceleft +2.1\textbraceright\_\textbraceleft -1.7\textbraceright\textbraceleft\textbraceright\textasciicircum\textbraceleft +3.8\textbraceright\_\textbraceleft -2.5\textbraceright{} and N\_\textbackslash nu\textasciicircum\textbraceleft\textbackslash rm eff\textbraceright =3.04 is allowed only at 2.4-sigma. The constraint on the dark energy equation of state is w=-1.04\textbackslash pm 0.06. The constraint on curvature is Omega\_k=-0.003\textbackslash pm 0.006. Cosmic strings limits are G\textbackslash mu {$<$}2.3 x 10\textasciicircum\textbraceleft -7\textbraceright{} at 95\% c.l. and correlated isocurvature models are also tightly constrained.},
  archiveprefix = {arXiv},
  langid = {american},
  keywords = {/finished},
  annotation = {Read\_Status: New\\
Read\_Status\_Date: 2024-12-24T15:24:27.659Z},
